<li>
g++ is actually a script which calls gcc with the appropriate options in
order to compile C++. Standard suffixes for C++ source files are: <code>.C</code>,
<code>.cc</code>, <code>.cxx</code>, <code>.cpp</code>, or <code>.c++</code>.
</li>
<li>
I recommend using g++ like so:<br />
<code class="cmd">g++ -Wall file1 [file2 [file3...]] -o output_file</code>
</li>
</points>

